#239 Misc
    :date: 2025-07-05 08:50
    :shortdes: Perfect brown lentils
    :tags: Food

.Several guests have recently asked me for my “recipe” for brown lentils.
I put that in quotes because it's so simple it barely counts as a recipe,
but it is indeed delicious (and cheap, easy, and suitable for almost any diet),
so I'm writing it down so I can send people here in the future.

.Ingredients, per ~2 cups cooked lentils:

<ul>
    <li>1 cup dry brown lentils (I like <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Non-GMO-Project-Verified-Non-Irradiated-Certified/dp/B001PEZLCW">Palouse Brand</a>)</li>
    <li>3 cups water</li>
    <li>1 heaping teaspoon coarse salt</li>
    <li>splash extra-virgin olive oil</li>
</ul>

.You can use vegetable broth instead of water if you really want to,
but good-quality lentils have plenty of flavor on their own.
The olive oil prevents the pot from foaming and makes the texture slightly smoother.

.Add all ingredients to a soup pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce to a bare simmer and simmer partially covered for 25 minutes.
The cooking time will vary a bit depending on the age of the lentils;
continue simmering until tender, checking every 5–10 minutes.
Brown lentils are more difficult to overcook than other types,
but still keep an eye on the stove; if you cook them well beyond tender, they'll fall apart into mush.

.Serve with coarsely ground pepper and lemon, and add rice, veggies, etc., as desired.
Don't skip the acid – lentils will never be excellent without it.
Lime, balsamic, apple cider vinegar, or tomatoes can work, but I think lemon is the best all-purpose choice.
If you go with citrus, use fresh wedges if you can –
the bottled juice contains bitter oil from the peel that doesn't go well with lentils.

.You can also make this in a pressure cooker if you don't want to bother with having something boiling on the stove,
but I think the texture is better when cooked low and slow.
Reduce the water by a cup or so and cook for 12 minutes on high pressure,
then wait for a natural release
(you can carefully release the remaining pressure after 10 minutes if you're in a hurry).


